body:
### Describe the bug

Let's take this example using the `Fruit` entity in the [hibernate-reactive-panache-quickstart](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus-quickstarts/tree/main/hibernate-reactive-panache-quickstart):

```
package org.acme.hibernate.orm.panache;

import io.quarkus.runtime.annotations.RegisterForReflection;

@RegisterForReflection
class Result {
	public final Double amount;

	public Result(Double amount) {
		this.amount = amount;
	}
}


Fruit
    .find( "select count(f) from Fruit f" )
    .project( Result.class )
    .singleResult();
```

It will throw the following exception:
```
Caused by: org.hibernate.hql.internal.ast.QuerySyntaxException: unexpected token: select near line 1, column 59 [SELECT new org.acme.hibernate.orm.panache.Result (amount) select count(f) from org.acme.hibernate.orm.panache.Fruit f]
```
It happens because Panache generates the wrong query.

The correct HQL query should be:
```
SELECT new org.acme.hibernate.orm.panache.Result(count(f)) from org.acme.hibernate.orm.panache.Fruit f
```
As a workaround, It works without the `.project( Result.class )`:
```
Fruit
    .find( "select new org.acme.hibernate.orm.panache.Result(count(f)) from Fruit f" )
    .singleResult();
```

Tested with Quarkus 2.9.2
When fixed, we should update [the SO question](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/72706797/quarkus-panache-reactive-select-single-column/72707284).
